  "prompt": "How much does it cost to complete undergraduation in Purdue University as an International student?",
  "response": "As of the 2023-2024 academic year, the estimated cost of attendance for international undergraduate students at Purdue University includes tuition, fees, and living expenses. Here\u2019s a breakdown of the costs:\n\n1. **Tuition and Fees**: For international undergraduate students, the estimated tuition and fees are around $31,000 to $38,000 per academic year, depending on the specific program and major.\n\n2. **Living Expenses**: This includes housing, meals, transportation, and personal expenses, which can total approximately $15,000 to $20,000 per year.\n\n3. **Health Insurance**: International students are required to have health insurance, which can add another $2,000 to $3,000 per year.\n\nOverall, the total estimated cost for an international undergraduate student at Purdue University can range from approximately $48,000 to $61,000 per year.\n\nKeep in mind that these figures are subject to change and can vary based on individual circumstances, lifestyle choices, and specific programs. It's always a good idea to check the official Purdue University website or contact the admissions office for the most current information.",
